lient based on the client’s overall wealth management plan the strategy takes considers the client’s risk tolerance and return objectives to design a portfolio that combines lower return lower risk investment classes such as high quality bonds with higher return seeking asset classes such as public and private equity investments most of the portfolio is invested with external investment managers and in scs funds the firm may also purchase securities directly to implement a portion of a wealth management programscs uses commercially available and proprietary databases to track investment managers in traditional and alternative asset classes scs recommends unaffiliated third party investment managers that specialize in the major asset classes including cash management fixed income large mid and smallcap stocks international securities and alternative investments such as private equity and hedge fundsscs fundsofhedge funds programs are designed to preserve and grow capital by producing absolute returns with reduced volatility and low correlation relative to the equity markets scs seeks to achieve strong relative performance through an intensive manager selection process while risk is managed through careful portfolio construction and diversification the scs invests fund assets among top tier hedge funds managed by new and established external managers scs may also invest a portion of certain funds assets directly in securities and other instrumentsin addition to traditional hedge fund strategies scs broadly classifies external managers into three categories growth uncorrelated and defensive growth managers typically have long net exposure to markets uncorrelated managers focus on security selection for their returns and do not exhibit a directional bias defensive managers construct portfolios designed to offer protection by producing outsized returns in down markets chief operating officer managing director   current scs financial services llc scs financial services llc provides investment management services it offers services in both traditional and alternative categories as well as tax trust and estate planning asset protection philanthropic strategy and family office services the company was founded by peter h mattoon antony j abbiati douglas r ederle stephen v kenney and william c walser in  and is headquartered in boston ma chief financial officer current scs hedged opportunities te fund llc scs hedged opportunities te fund llc is a closedend investment fundinvestment trust the company was founded on august   and is headquartered in boston ma headinvestment operations  technology prior   grantham mayo van otterloo  co llc gmo founded in  is a privately held global investment management firm servicing clients in the corporate public endowment and foundation marketplaces as of december   we managed  billion in client assets using a blend of traditional judgments with innovative quantitative methods to find undervalued securities and markets our success in consistently providing value added performance across a broad range of asset classes is founded on several key factors that include discipline value orientation investment research and constant innovation see gmo qualities below our broadbased value added over benchmarks has led many of our clients to request that we allocate assets and advise them on a global scale chief financial officer prior scudder weisel capital funds director of finance global investment operations prior deutsche asset management inc deutsche asset management inc part of deutsche bank ag is a company headquartered in new york ny that provides asset management and investment advisory fund advisor prior ssga funds management inc ssga funds management ssga fm uses quantitative methods as well as an industryspecific bottomup investment approach to select stocks the firms mutual funds and institutional portfolios follow the same management style they offer a broad range of strategies including active enhanced and passive equity active  passive debt cash management multiasset class solutions real estate including direct real estate senior loans managed futures and private equity cash and real estate the firms active enhanced  passive are designed to outperform relative to benchmarks while maintaining appropriate risk exposure active equity strategies include enhanced equity and active quantitative strategies the strategies cover marketcap and style segments of the market including largecap core largecap growth largecap value midcap smallcap smallcap value allcap and longshort equity they also manage longshort and longshort market neutral strategiesssga fms active  passive debt strategies seek to meet clients’ objectives by controlling risk while diversifying sources of excess return the firm offers a range of investment styles from passive to active short to long duration taxexempt sovereign to high yield and single country to global the strategies typically use a stratified sampling methodology to build portfolios with the same characteristics as the index using quantitative and fundamental methodsssga fms cash strategies seek to generate current income while preserving capital and liquidity by investing in diversified portfolios of shortterm securitiesssga fms multiasset class strategies employ an asset allocation model as means of diversification and seeks to position assets among major investment categories the goal is to manage risk and enhance returnsssga fm is an advisor to funds that employ both passive and actively managed reits investing strategies they also offer direct real estate investment strategiesssga fm is an advisor to a fund that employs senior loan investing strategies an unaffiliated subadvisor directs the investments of the fund ssga fms managed futures strategy allocates assets using two approaches a managed futures strategy and a fixed income strategy the managed futures strategy seeks to capture returns tied to global macroeconomic trends in the commodity futures markets taking both long and short positions the fixed income strategy is designed to generate interest income and capital appreciation to add diversification to the returns generated by the managed futures strategyssga fms private equity strategies focus on rigorous partner selection thorough evaluation of quality investment opportunities and fundamental researchdriven research the strategies make direct or coinvestments across sectors as well as fund investments fund advisor prior state street global advisors research founded in  state street global advisors advanced research center is the research arm of state street global advisors the firm is a subsidiary of state street corp nyse stt a leading provider of financial services to institutional investors including corporations retirement plans public funds endowments foundations and thirdparty distributors they provide quantitative research and develop quantitative models for active strategies in equities fixedincome asset allocation and currencies boards  committees corporate boards ▾ director tenure unconfirmed scs hedged opportunities te fund llc scs hedged opportunities te fund llc is a closedend investment fundinvestment trust the company was founded on august   and is headquartered in boston ma transactions details hidden scs institutional investment fund spc for the account of scs institutional fund i segregated portfolio raised money in a private placement transaction details hidden scs core fixed income plus fund llc raised money in a private placement transaction details hidden scs special situations fund ltd raised money in a private placement transaction details hidden scs hedged opportunities te fund llc raised money in a private placement transaction details hidden scs fixed income strategies fund llc raised money in a private placement transaction see  more listings with relsci professional start my free trial ➤ see  more awards  honors professional certification cfa chartered 